{"type":"message","id":"1746b1c1","parentId":"b513360f","timestamp":"2026-03-19T11:10:32.081Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context monitor is reporting that the main session has 73% context usage (145,742/200,000 tokens), which exceeds the 60% threshold. The script recommends starting a new session. Since this is running as a cron job with a Context Monitor label, I should just report this as an informational heartbeat check - no action needed unless the user wants to do something about it. I'll reply HEARTBEAT_OK with the status info.\n\nActually, the system prompt says I should follow HEARTBEAT.md strictly. Let me check if it exists and what it says.","thinkingSignature":"5355d4ccb677a4d4db18ac4b3cbb62f2b6edbf8a01b169d846f0fe41fc862bec"},{"type":"text","text":"📊 **Context Monitor Report**\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| **Context Usage** | 73% (145,742 / 200,000 tokens) |\n| **Threshold** | 60% |\n| **Status** | ⚠️ Warning — exceeds threshold |\n\nNo action taken — this is an informational heartbeat. Reply `HEARTBEAT_OK` if no further action needed, or let me know if you'd like me to start a new session to reset context."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1263,"output":222,"cacheRead":37011,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38496,"cost":{"input":0.0005052,"output":0.000333,"cacheRead":0.00148044,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0023186400000000003}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773918624144}}
